---
import Section from './Section.astro';
import SectionHeader from './SectionHeader.astro';
import PromptBox from './PromptBox.astro';

import faceSideProfile from '~/content/prompts/face-side-profile.txt?raw';
import faceBackView from '~/content/prompts/face-back-view.txt?raw';
import eyeCloseup from '~/content/prompts/eye-closeup.txt?raw';

import fullBodySideProfile from '~/content/prompts/full-body-side-profile.txt?raw';
import fullBodyBackView from '~/content/prompts/full-body-back-view.txt?raw';
---

<Section>

  <SectionHeader
    eyebrow="Phase 3"
    title="Generate Every Reference Angle"
    description="Create a complete set of reference images covering every important viewing angle of your character. These references will significantly improve character consistency across future AI image and video generations."
    maxWidth="lg"
  />

  <div class="mt-8 max-w-3xl">

    <!-- STEP 1 -->

    <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">
      Step 1 — Face Reference Set
    </h2>

    <ol class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-300">

      <li>
        <strong class="text-white">1.</strong>
        Always attach the <strong class="text-white">Master Reference Portrait</strong> as the reference image.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong class="text-white">2.</strong>
        Use the corresponding prompt below to generate each new facial angle while preserving the exact same identity.
      </li>

      <li>
        <strong class="text-white">3.</strong>
        Generate and approve each reference image before moving on to the next one.
      </li>

    </ol>

    <PromptBox
  title="Right / Left Side Prompt"
  prompt={faceSideProfile}
/>

    <PromptBox
  title="Face Back View Prompt"
  prompt={faceBackView}
/>

    <PromptBox
  title="Eye Close-up Prompt"
  prompt={eyeCloseup}
/>

    <p class="mt-8 text-sm italic leading-7 text-gray-400">
      You should now have five reference images of your character's face: a Front View, Left Profile, Right Profile, Back View and Eye Close-up.
    </p>

    <!-- STEP 2 -->

    <div class="mt-12 border-t border-white/10 pt-12">

      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-white">
        Step 2 — Body Reference Set
      </h2>

      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">
        Now let's do the same for the full body.
      </p>

      <ol class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-300">

        <li>
          <strong class="text-white">1.</strong>
          Always attach the <strong class="text-white">Master Reference Full Body</strong> together with the corresponding Face Reference image for the angle you want to generate.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong class="text-white">2.</strong>
          Use the corresponding prompt below to generate each full-body angle while preserving the exact same character identity.
        </li>

        <li>
          <strong class="text-white">3.</strong>
          Generate and approve each reference image before moving on to the next one.
        </li>

      </ol>

      <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">
        For example:
      </p>

      <ul class="mt-4 space-y-1 text-sm leading-6 text-gray-300">

        <li>• Left Body Profile → Master Reference Full Body + Left Face Profile</li>

        <li>• Right Body Profile → Master Reference Full Body + Right Face Profile</li>

        <li>• Back Body View → Master Reference Full Body + Back Face View</li>

      </ul>

      <p class="mt-6 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">
        This approach ensures the AI preserves both the character's body proportions and the correct head orientation, resulting in much greater character consistency.
      </p>

      <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">
        If any reference image looks inconsistent, regenerate only that specific angle before proceeding to the next step.
      </p>

      <PromptBox
  title="Full Body Side Profile Prompt"
  prompt={fullBodySideProfile}
/>

      <PromptBox
  title="Full Body Back View Prompt"
  prompt={fullBodyBackView}
/>

      <p class="mt-8 text-sm italic leading-7 text-gray-400">
        You should now have four full-body reference images of your character: a Front View, Left Profile, Right Profile and Back View.
      </p>

    </div>

  </div>

</Section>